{"<"} div id =' experience ' {">"}

{"<"} p class =' coursework ' {">"}

Some of my coursework includes Algorithmic Game Theory, Computer Architecture, Operating Systems, Data Structures and Algorithms, Scalable and Cloud Computing, Databases and Information Systems, Software Design, Discrete Mathematics, Number Theory, as well as Automata, Computability, and Complexity.

{" p {">"}

{"<"} p class =' technicalSkills ' {">"}

I am comfortable with Java, HTML, Node.js, C, LaTeX, SQL, Git, Agile Development (Scrum), Linux/OSX, Amazon EMR, QA, and automated testing. I am a beginner at Python, OCaml, React, MongoDB, Android Development, and C++.

{" "} {" p {">"}

{" "} {"<"} p class =' professionalExperience ' {">"}

This past summer I was a software development intern at Ellucian. I spent this time working directly inbetween the devs and the QA team to optimize the automated testing suite and workflow.

{" "} {" p {">"}

{" "} {"<"} p class =' interests ' {">"}

As of late, the projects that have given me the most joy have involved full-stack development. I very much enjoy getting to work on all aspects of a project. My interests currently lie in algorithm design, game theory, software optimization, and humanitarian software development. Namely, one of the things I am most passionate about is making computer science both more accessible and more approachable.

{" "} {" p {">"}

{"

"}

My current outlook on engineering has been largely shaped by the time I spent in Rwanda this past summer. This time was spent at the Gashora Girls Academy of Science and Technology, teaching computer science and helping students with a handful of their own projects. One of the most notable projects was using a Raspberry Pi to automate a hydroponic tomato garden (it is very difficult to get tomatoes to grow naturally in Rwanda, given the climate). My time at the academy left me with an understanding of the impact computer science can have on the lives of others. Now that I am getting ready to start my professional career, I am eager to design software that leaves a positive impact on the world and on those around me.
